Subject Black Screen of Death Windows Novell From Hi there We are running a node Token ring with Windows and Novell Every once in a while we run into The Black Screen of Death a phrase coined by Robert Cringely in a recent InfoWorld Basically sometimes when you quit Windows the screen goes black and you get a nice little flashing cursor in the top left corner of your Also sometimes when you exit to DOS the same effect Cringely hints that Microsoft and or Novell has a patch for Windows' virtual interrupt controller that may solve Neither company seems to know what I am talking about when I call Has anyone else noticed this phenomenon Is there a fix for it Any response is Peter Sweeney